      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R2023 R1 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures, V&V test suite reports, and ISO 9001 certification. Internal FDA software QA procedures were applied to pre- and post-processing scripts. Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmarks and patch tests must be documented and passed.",
      "rationale": "Standard Ansys benchmark suite including patch tests, beam bending analytical comparisons, and contact patch tests were executed and passed. Results archived in the simulation record. Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study required demonstrating less than 5% change in QoI between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the screw-rod-vertebral body assembly. Construct stiffness QoI changed by less than 2.1% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI reported as 1.4%. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria documented and energy balance verified.",
      "rationale": "Force residual convergence tolerance set to 1e-4; displacement tolerance 1e-5. Energy balance checked across all load steps. No unconverged increments in production runs. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation execution checklist and independent reviewer sign-off required.",
      "rationale": "A structured simulation execution checklist was completed for each model run. An independent engineer reviewed boundary condition setup, material assignment, and contact definitions. No use errors identified. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection must be justified relative to the physics of the application and supported by literature.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum FEA is well established for metallic spinal implants under ASTM F1717 quasi-static loading. Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) and stainless steel material models validated against NIST reference data. Geometric nonlinearity included for large-displacement screw bending. Model form selection documented with literature support. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to measurement data or certified material specifications.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength sourced from certified mill test reports for each production lot. Screw and rod geometry measured by CMM on production parts. Coefficient of friction for titanium-on-titanium contact set to 0.3 per literature consensus. All inputs logged in simulation record. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples must be production-representative and sample size must support statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative screws and rods. Sample size supports 90% confidence interval on mean stiffness. Lot traceability documented. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of loading conditions relevant to the intended use.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single applied displacement rate and a single offset distance per ASTM F1717. The standard does not require multiple conditions, but V&V 40 factor assessment identifies this as a limitation relative to the range of in vivo loading scenarios. Achieved level is below required level; this shortfall is acknowledged in the overall credibility assessment and accepted given the regulatory precedent for F1717 as a standardised bench test."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental test inputs.",
      "rationale": "Geometric dimensions, material lots, and assembly torque values used in FEA were matched to the physical test specimens through direct measurement and traceability records. Boundary conditions replicate the F1717 fixture constraints. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E-metric or normalised RMS error) must be computed and reported.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness predicted by FEA ensemble falls within the 95% confidence interval of experimental measurements for 10 of 11 specimens. Normalised RMS error across ensemble is 4.8%. E-metric computed per ASME V&V 10.1. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the regulatory question of interest.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak screw bending moment are the primary QoIs. Both are directly linked to the regulatory performance criterion (structural integrity under worst-case loading) and are the quantities reported in the 510(k) submission. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be sufficiently similar to the intended use scenario to support extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the ASTM F1717 bench test that constitutes the regulatory submission test. The FEA model geometry, loading, and boundary conditions are identical to the submission scenario. Relevance to the clinical research application of this model is supported by the correspondence between bench-test loading and worst-case in vivo compression-bending. Required level achieved."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk level 3. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as a standardised single-condition bench test and the conservative nature of the worst-case loading scenario. Overall credibility is sufficient to support use of the FEA model for the stated regulatory purpose. The model has been applied in clinical research to support device design decisions; the assessment team considers the aggregate evidence adequate for the intended submission context.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
